<dl id="n40063d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40063d">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40063d"> 63(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mullah / (schoolmaster)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ritual, properly so called, there was none; congregational prayers were merely those of the individual en masse and the only admitted approach to a sacerdotal order were the Olema or scholars learned in the legistic and the Mullah or schoolmaster. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 182</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Cf. <cite>FW</cite> 193.18: And he had it from the Mullah.</mm> </dd></dl>
